09/03/2009
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police seized 10kg of heroin Saturday (March 7th), arresting three people suspected of producing and trafficking the drugs.
Police identified them only as Milan M., Danijela S. and Branislav J., all residents of Belgrade.
According to preliminary investigations, Milan M. was buying large amounts of heroin in Bulgaria for resale in Belgrade.
(Vecernje Novosti - 09/03/09;
B92 - 08/03/09)
